body:
I believe that Yosys (git SHA a93fcec) fails to handle the following example correctly:

```
module Main_fir_sfir(result);
  output signed [9:0] result;

  wire signed [9:0] intermediate [0:2];

  function integer depth2Index;
    input integer depth;

    depth2Index = depth;
  endfunction

  assign intermediate[depth2Index(2)] = 0;  
  assign result = intermediate[2];
endmodule
```

Specifically, when I show the schematic using the show command, intermediate[2] is not driven, but it should be driven by the second to last line of the module. As a result, when I optimise it with opt_clean -purge, the whole circuit disappears.

This is a simplification of the Verilog generated by the [Clash](http://www.clash-lang.org/) compiler for the FIR filter example on that page.

It works correctly if I replace the depthToIndex(2) call with the literal 2. i.e. I remove the depthToIndex function call on the second to last line.

code_blocks:
module Main_fir_sfir(result);
  output signed [9:0] result;

  wire signed [9:0] intermediate [0:2];

  function integer depth2Index;
    input integer depth;

    depth2Index = depth;
  endfunction

  assign intermediate[depth2Index(2)] = 0;  
  assign result = intermediate[2];
endmodule
